587. For the construction non aequom quin comp. mirum quin, v. 495. In both quin has its original sense ‘why not’. It may be translated ‘ except that ⁵, but the original sense can be distinctly traced. Plautus uses quin in very many phrases and sometimes with considerable freedom.
